/*1. Input / Output Statement using Scanner
Problem:
Create a Java program that takes a user's name, age, and city as input using the Scanner class, and prints a greeting message:

"Hello <name>, you are <age> years old and live in <city>."*/

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner in = new Scanner(System.in); // Create Scanner object

        // Input name
        System.out.print("Enter your name: ");
        String name = in.nextLine();

        // Input age
        System.out.print("Enter your age: ");
        int age = in.nextInt();
        in.nextLine();  // Consume the leftover newline character

        // Input city
        System.out.print("Enter your city: ");
        String city = in.nextLine();

        // Output greeting
        System.out.println("Hello " + name + ", you are " + age + " years old and live in " + city + ".");
    }
}
